<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><span style=3D"font-size:1.0pt; color:wh=
ite">Good morning Grant, Thank you so much for your email and for sharing th=
e process document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, Devonport. I r=
eally appreciate your effort to outline
 the framework and the chance to work together on this.</span><span style=3D=
"font-size:1.0pt; font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif; color:white">=E2=
=80=8A</span><span style=3D"font-size:1.0pt; color:white"></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><span style=3D"font-size:1.0pt; color:wh=
ite"></span></p>
</div>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Good morning Grant,</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Thank you so much for your email and for s=
haring the process document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, Devo=
nport. I really appreciate your effort to outline the framework and the chan=
ce to work together on this. It=E2=80=99s
 great to see the team involved, and I=E2=80=99d love your guidance on how w=
e can move forward smoothly.</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99ve looked over the process map a=
nd have a few thoughts to ensure we get this right, especially around safety=
 and planning. I=E2=80=99ve heard from firefighters about significant fire d=
amage and smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially thought
 to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which has me concerned ab=
out the house=E2=80=99s condition.</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Could we please consider the following adj=
ustments?</p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quo=
t;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Clarify Claim Scope</span></strong>: Is this the p=
lan for both house and contents claims? If so, should it therefore be linked=
 to both policy numbers to ensure all coverage
 is included?</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span style=3D=
"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Prioritize Health &amp; Safety</s=
pan></strong>: I=E2=80=99d feel more comfortable if we scheduled independent=
 assessments (electrical, structural, gas, moisture/mould) before any major
 work, alongside the July 9 asbestos survey. The master electrician=E2=80=99=
s finding that the property is uninhabitable due to electrical hazards is a k=
ey concern.</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span style=3D"=
font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Assessment-Only Focus</span></stro=
ng>: As previously expressed, could we limit initial tasks to enabling damag=
e assessment (e.g., securing the site, debris removal) rather
 than repairs (e.g., upstairs decontamination, curtain cleaning)? This would=
 allow for a thorough evaluation and mutual agreement on remediation. The pl=
anned upstairs cleaning (July 21-25) feels premature for these reasons:
</li></ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<ol start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">We need to assess damage before repair t=
o preserve evidence.</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">If the gas uni=
t (likely damaged) requires removal, the ceiling may need cutting, necessita=
ting re-cleaning.</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">The electrician=E2=
=80=99s uninhabitable ruling requires electrical work first.</li><li class=3D=
"x_MsoNormal" style=3D"">Firefighters switched off water (possibly gas?) and=
 electricity, which must be assessed and remediated.</li><li class=3D"x_MsoN=
ormal" style=3D"">With 4 pets and hybrid work, noisy basement/deck/roof work=
 makes living there untenable until completed.</li></ol>
</ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D""><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quo=
t;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Asbestos Survey Details</span></strong>: While I=E2=
=80=99m supportive of the July 9 survey, could you please share who will con=
duct it, the scope and tests involved, and how I can
 independently verify the results? Also, can the funding for this be covered=
 under the claim preparation provision?</li><li class=3D"x_MsoNormal" style=3D=
""><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Structur=
al Engineer Guidelines</span></strong>: I previously asked about guidelines f=
or paying a structural engineer, as per the provision for claim preparation.=
 Could you
 please provide these, as I believe an independent assessment should precede=
 any repair work?</li></ul>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99d be grateful if you could provi=
de a revised plan with a written timeline for expert sign-offs and re-occupa=
tion only after safety is assured, preferably via email, by July 15, 2025. I=
=E2=80=99m really looking forward to working with
 you for a safe and fair outcome.</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Kind regards,</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Raffaella del Prete</p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">&nbsp;</p>
